      "writtenOn": "2020-11-13T00:48:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "To land changes like this, we have to do a little #ifdef dance with Chromium.  I\u0027d expect to follow something like \"Method 2\" described here: https://skia.org/dev/chrome/changes\n\nWe\u0027d update Chromium\u0027s tests when landing the Chromium part of the change that #defines the symbol, and update Skia\u0027s tests when removing the #ifdef (assuming we wanted it on by default for everyone).  (Since it would affect a large number of tests in Chrome, we\u0027d probably want to do the [NeedsRebaseline] trick, as mentioned here: \nhttps://skia.org/dev/chrome/blink.)\n\nMy bigger concern: given the location of the code, this doesn\u0027t easily lend itself to a runtime flag to turn it on or off in Chrome, so we\u0027d probably have to land it without going through an \u0027experimental\u0027 phase.  Do you see this as a problem, Dominik?",
      "parentUuid": "efcb9306_856ce303",
      "revId": "7adaa208d5812befa8355ded97d2731061a6ee14",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
